From 20740690152382392a11ce72c7155e18a6ffc641 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Henke <henke.mike@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 13:43:24 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] fix(fallback): add grace window so fallback-aborted
 background tasks reconcile (#765)

PR #769 guarded backgroundJobBoard.drop() in onSessionDeleted with the strict
isFallbackInProgress flag, but that flag is cleared in the finally block of
tryFallback/tryFallbackWithAbort right after promptAsync returns. The abort's
late session.deleted (and the aborted task's cancelled/error status) arrive
asynchronously after the finally, so the guard was ineffective: the board job
was dropped or overwritten with a terminal cancelled/error state. When the
fallback re-prompt's response made the session go idle, board.get(id).state
!== 'running', so the idle reconciliation (which requires running) never fired
and the task was reported cancelled despite the agent having responded.

Add a separate time-based grace window (wasFallbackRecent) that stays true for
FALLBACK_GRACE_WINDOW_MS (5s) after a successful fallback re-prompt, distinct
from the strict in-flight isFallbackInProgress flag (which must clear in
finally so the genuine fallback-response idle still reconciles). Wire it into
task-session-manager to:

(a) keep the onSessionDeleted drop guard effective against late
    abort-induced session.deleted (!isFallbackInProgress && !wasFallbackRecent)
(b) suppress spurious fallback-induced cancelled/error status updates in both
    the injected-completion path (updateBackgroundJobFromOutput) and the
    synchronous tool.execute.after status path, so the job stays running for
    idle reconciliation.

The grace window is armed only after promptAsync is accepted (not on
chain-exhaustion aborts), so a real terminated session still records its
cancelled/error status.
