    - Remembers injected terminal jobs to reconcile them on parent idle events
 
 5. **Lifecycle Events (`event`)**
-   - `session.created`: Adds new task IDs to pending managed set
-   - `session.idle` / `session.status` (idle): Reconciles injected terminal jobs for the parent session
+   - `session.created`: Adds new task IDs to pending managed set; registers a background job from the pending call when `tool.execute.after` was missed (net for #765), with phantom-running-job cleanup during fallback
+   - `session.idle` / `session.status` (idle): Reconciles injected terminal jobs for the parent session; also reconciles a still-running child job from idle (guarded by `isFallbackInProgress` so transient fallback aborts don't prematurely complete it)
    - `session.status` (busy): Marks sessions as running from live session state
-   - `session.deleted`: Clears job state, child jobs, and pending call records for the session
+   - `session.deleted`: Clears job state, child jobs, and pending call records for the session — guarded by `isFallbackInProgress` AND `wasFallbackRecent` so a late abort-induced deletion during/after a foreground fallback doesn't drop a still-live job (issue #765)
+   - `onJobTerminal`: Notifies the orchestrator (via `promptAsync`) when a background job reaches a terminal state, so it re-evaluates its conversation even when no child idle fires
+   - Spurious cancelled/error status arriving within `wasFallbackRecent` (injected completions and `tool.execute.after`) is suppressed so the job stays running for the genuine fallback-response idle (issue #765)
 
 ### Data & Control Flow
 
